post_cb({"5500070": {"ParentId": "5500057", "CommentCount": "8", "CreationDate": "2011-03-31T12:48:12.837", "OwnerUserId": "500104", "PostTypeId": "2", "Id": "5500070", "Score": "31", "Body": "<p>A pointer to a static member function is just a normal function pointer. <code>typedef void (*PPMF2)()</code>. You assign it to a static member function like you assign any function pointer, only that the static member function is inside the class scope:</p>\n<pre><code>PPMF2 myfunc = &amp;MyClass::StaticMemberFunc;\n</code></pre>\n", "LastActivityDate": "2011-03-31T12:48:12.837"}, "5500057": {"CommentCount": "4", "ViewCount": "20448", "PostTypeId": "1", "LastEditorUserId": "560648", "CreationDate": "2011-03-31T12:47:28.687", "LastActivityDate": "2016-10-05T07:27:56.777", "Title": "How to define a function pointer pointing to a static member function?", "LastEditDate": "2013-01-31T06:20:18.353", "Id": "5500057", "Score": "20", "Body": "<pre><code>#include \"stdafx.h\"\n\nclass Person;\ntypedef void (Person::*PPMF)();\n\n// error C2159: more than one storage class specified\ntypedef static void (Person::*PPMF2)();  \n\nclass Person\n{\npublic:\n    static PPMF verificationFUnction()\n    { \n        return &amp;Person::verifyAddress; \n    }\n\n    // error C2440: 'return' : cannot convert from \n    // 'void (__cdecl *)(void)' to 'PPMF2'\n    PPMF2 verificationFUnction2()               \n    { \n        return &amp;Person::verifyAddress2; \n    }\nprivate:\n    void verifyAddress() {}\n\n    static void verifyAddress2() {}\n};\n\nint _tmain(int argc, _TCHAR* argv[])\n{\n    Person scott;\n\n    PPMF pmf = scott.verificationFUnction();\n    (scott.*pmf)();\n    return 0;\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>Question: I need to define a function pointer PPMF2 to pointing to a static member function verifyAddress2. How can I do it?</p>\n<pre><code>#include \"stdafx.h\"\n\nclass Person;\ntypedef void (Person::*PPMF)();\ntypedef void (Person::*PPMF2)();\n\nclass Person\n{\npublic:\n    static PPMF verificationFUnction()\n    { \n        return &amp;Person::verifyAddress; \n    }\n    PPMF2 verificationFUnction2()\n    { \n        return &amp;Person::verifyAddress2; \n    }\nprivate:\n    void verifyAddress() {}\n\n    static void verifyAddress2() {}\n};\n\nint _tmain(int argc, _TCHAR* argv[])\n{\n    Person scott;\n\n    PPMF pmf = scott.verificationFUnction();\n    (scott.*pmf)();\n\n    return 0;\n}\n</code></pre>\n", "Tags": "<c++>", "OwnerUserId": "391104", "AnswerCount": "4"}, "5500117": {"ParentId": "5500057", "PostTypeId": "2", "CommentCount": "4", "CreationDate": "2011-03-31T12:50:56.610", "Score": "1", "LastEditorUserId": "269943", "LastEditDate": "2011-03-31T13:21:05.217", "Id": "5500117", "OwnerUserId": "269943", "Body": "<p>If the function is static it does not require a (implicit) <code>this</code> pointer to be invoked. Therefore, a pointer to a static member function is not the same as a member function pointer:</p>\n<pre><code>#include \"stdafx.h\"\n\nclass Person;\ntypedef void (Person::*PPMF)();\ntypedef /*static*/ void (*PPMF2)();\n\nclass Person\n{\npublic:\n    static PPMF verificationFUnction()\n    { \n        return &amp;Person::verifyAddress; \n    }\n    PPMF2 verificationFUnction2() \n    { \n        return &amp;Person::verifyAddress2; \n    }\nprivate:\n    void verifyAddress() {}\n\n    static void verifyAddress2() {}\n};\n\nint _tmain(int argc, _TCHAR* argv[])\n{\n    Person scott;\n\n    PPMF pmf = scott.verificationFUnction();\n    (*pmf)();\n    return 0;\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>EDIT:</p>\n<p>removed the offending static from the typedef.</p>\n", "LastActivityDate": "2011-03-31T13:21:05.217"}, "39867846": {"ParentId": "5500057", "CommentCount": "1", "CreationDate": "2016-10-05T07:27:56.777", "OwnerUserId": "6924903", "PostTypeId": "2", "Id": "39867846", "Score": "0", "Body": "<pre><code>#include&lt;iostream&gt;\n\nusing namespace std;\nclass A\n{\nprivate:\n    int x,y;\n    static int a;\npublic:\n    A()\n    {\n        x = 10;\n        y = 11;\n    }\n    ~A()\n    {\n\n    }\n\n    void displayNonStatic()\n    {\n        cout&lt;&lt;x&lt;&lt;\"  \"&lt;&lt;y&lt;&lt;endl;\n    }\n\n    void displayStatic()\n    {\n        cout&lt;&lt;a&lt;&lt;endl;\n    }\n};\n\nint A::a = 12;\nint main()\n{\n    typedef void (A::*NonStatic)(void);\n    typedef void (A::*Static)(void);\n    A a1;\n\n    NonStatic _nstatic = &amp;A::displayNonStatic ;\n    Static _static = &amp;A::displayStatic;\n\n    // Always make sure that call to the pointer to the member functions is made within the context of the instance.\n\n//Correct way to call the pointer within the context of the instance \" a1 \" .\n    (a1.*_nstatic)();\n    (a1.*_static)();\n//Error case given below, the pointer is not called within the context of the instance\n  // (*_nstatic)(); -&gt;error\n  // (*_static)(); -&gt;error\n    getchar();\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>Refer to the  <a href=\"https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/z72c1dfd.aspx\" rel=\"nofollow\">link</a> for more information.</p>\n", "LastActivityDate": "2016-10-05T07:27:56.777"}, "30949326": {"ParentId": "5500057", "CommentCount": "0", "CreationDate": "2015-06-20T01:14:18.867", "OwnerUserId": "1154447", "PostTypeId": "2", "Id": "30949326", "Score": "3", "Body": "<p>About static member function guarantees:</p>\n<p>\u0421++ ISO/IEC 14882 2003-10-15 says that</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_5500057_30949326_0\">5.2.2 There are two kinds of function call: ordinary function call and member function 57) (9.3) call....</p>\n<p id=\"so_5500057_30949326_1\">57) A static member function (9.4) is an ordinary function.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Theoretically static-member-functions can have another calling convention.\nBut standart allow us to leverage on such thing...</p>\n<p>Answer:\ntypedef void (Person::*PPMF2)() =&gt; typedef void (*PPMF2)()</p>\n", "LastActivityDate": "2015-06-20T01:14:18.867"}, "bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_5500057_30949326_1": {"section_id": 228, "quality": 0.8, "length": 4}, "so_5500057_30949326_0": {"section_id": 576, "quality": 0.5833333333333334, "length": 7}}, "n3337": {"so_5500057_30949326_1": {"section_id": 5756, "quality": 1.0, "length": 5}, "so_5500057_30949326_0": {"section_id": 5756, "quality": 0.9166666666666666, "length": 11}}, "n4659": {"so_5500057_30949326_1": {"section_id": 236, "quality": 0.8, "length": 4}, "so_5500057_30949326_0": {"section_id": 599, "quality": 0.5833333333333334, "length": 7}}}});